# The nearest iron ore position remains the same at (-14.5, 26.5), indicating that we are indeed at the correct location.
# Since we can't harvest from this position, it is possible that the resource is not within our current reach or that we need to adjust our position slightly.

# Let's move closer to the iron ore position to ensure we can harvest it.
move_to(new_iron_position)  # Move to the iron ore position again.
print(f"Moved to Iron Ore Position: {new_iron_position}") 

# After moving, we will attempt to harvest the iron ore again.
harvest_resource(new_iron_position, quantity=10)  # Attempt to harvest 10 units of iron ore.
print(f"Inventory changed to {inspect_inventory()}")
